# Innovation challenge

![](data:image/png;base64,)

## Overview
Innovation challenges are a tactic used to detect solutions to development challenges by soliciting innovative ideas and solutions from various stakeholders.

## Purpose
The purpose of innovation challenges is to address complex development problems that cannot be solved through traditional means, by leveraging the creativity and expertise of external partners and solution developers.

## How it works
An innovation challenge typically involves identifying a specific development challenge, making an open call for solutions, evaluating entries based on predetermined criteria, and awarding the best proposal for further development.

## Requirements
This method requires conditions where there are no known solutions to the challenge, and buy-in from programme and project teams within the country office. Solution developers must also be aware that they will not own intellectual property rights to any of the solutions they develop.

## Reflections
It is essential to have clear objectives and deliverables when using innovation challenges, and to scout potential partners and informally reach out to them to gauge their support before launching a challenge.

## Related methods (if any)
Innovation challenges are often used in conjunction with co-creation and solutions mapping.
